<article class="DELETE docs-container">
  <header class="header-bg-dark d-sm-flex justify-content-sm-between
                align-items-sm-center py-2 px-3">
    <h2 class="pb-2 pb-sm-0 m-0">Delete a Herb</h2>
    <code class="m-0">
      <b>DELETE</b> /herbs/:id
    </code>
  </header>

  <section class="p-3 inner-docs-container">
    <p>This method allows users to delete an existing herb.</p>

    <h3 class="subheader-bold">Request</h3>

    <p>https://theteaapi.herokuapp.com/api/v1/herbs/<em>:id</em></p>
    <p>OR</p>
    <p>https://theteaapi.herokuapp.com/api/v1/herbs/<em>herb-name</em></p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        The headers must include a valid authentication token.
      </li>
      <li>
        :id is the id the herb to delete. You can also use the herb's name.
      </li>
      <li>
        The body is omitted.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="subheader-bold">Response</h3>

    <p>If succeeds, returns an empty response with the status 204.</p>

    <p>
      <code>
    Status: 204 No Content
      </code>
    </p>
  </section>
</article>
